🌍 World Happiness Analysis: Insights & Trends
📌 Project Overview
This project provides a comprehensive analysis of the World Happiness Report (2015-2024). The goal is to explore the factors that contribute to global well-being and identify trends over the last decade. Using Python, I performed Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) to uncover how economic, social, and health factors influence happiness scores across different continents.

🔍 Key Questions Answered
Economic Impact: Does a higher GDP per capita always lead to a higher happiness score?

Global Trends: How has world happiness evolved over the past 10 years?

Social Support: How significant is the role of social support and healthy life expectancy?

Population Factor: Is there a correlation between country population size and happiness?

🛠️ Tools & Technologies
Language: Python 🐍

Libraries: * Pandas for data manipulation.

Seaborn & Matplotlib for static visualizations.

Plotly for interactive geo-spatial maps.

Framework: Google Colab / Kaggle Notebook.

📊 Analysis Steps (The Data Analysis Process)
Ask: Defined the business task and key questions.

Prepare: Collected and structured the data from the World Happiness Report.

Process: Cleaned the data, handled missing values, and merged datasets.

Analyze: Conducted correlation analysis and trend identification.

Share: Created visualizations to tell the story behind the numbers.

Act: Provided final insights and recommendations based on the findings.

🚀 How to use this Dataset
You can use the provided Python Notebook to:

See how the data was cleaned and prepared.

Interact with the global maps to see happiness scores by country.

Modify the code to include more recent data or different variables.

